Pre-Game Insights: New Zealand won by 99 runs in the previous match against England.
Tim Southee and Lockie Ferguson are likely to be fit for the match against Netherlands, while Logan van Beek might miss out due to a hamstring injury.
Netherlands have a strong record against Associate nations, having never lost a World Cup game against them.
Netherlands showed spunk in their first game of the tournament, finishing second in the World Cup Qualifier behind three Full Member nations.
Netherlands have been in Hyderabad longer than New Zealand and are more familiar with the conditions.
New Zealand have won all four previous ODIs against Netherlands, with three of those games by a margin of 100+ runs.
